---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Houston at the 2026 World Cup — A Fan's Guide to NRG Matches | HtownGuide"
  description="Visiting Houston for the 2026 FIFA World Cup? Where to stay near NRG Stadium, watch parties, getting around in summer heat, and what to do between matches."
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 pt-20 pb-12">
    <span class="block text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)] mb-4">June 11 – July 19, 2026</span>
    <h1 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-5xl sm:text-6xl md:text-7xl tracking-tight leading-[0.95] max-w-4xl text-balance">
      Houston at the <em class="italic font-normal text-[color:var(--color-clay)]">World Cup</em>.
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-8 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)] text-pretty">
      Houston is one of eleven U.S. host cities for the 2026 FIFA World Cup, with seven matches scheduled at NRG Stadium between June 11 and July 19. If you're flying in for a match — or three — this is what we'd tell a friend before they came.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-12">
    <div class="grid gap-px bg-[color:var(--color-ink)]/10 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8">
        <span class="block text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[color:var(--color-clay)] mb-2">Venue</span>
        <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl mb-2">NRG Stadium</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">
          Air-conditioned, retractable roof. Capacity ~72,000. Home of the Houston Texans. Three miles south of downtown.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8">
        <span class="block text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[color:var(--color-clay)] mb-2">Weather</span>
        <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl mb-2">Hot & humid</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">
          Daily highs 90–95°F with high humidity. Bring breathable clothes, plan indoor activities midday, hydrate before matches.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8">
        <span class="block text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[color:var(--color-clay)] mb-2">Airport</span>
        <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl mb-2">IAH or HOU</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">
          Houston has two — George Bush Intercontinental (IAH, larger, international) and Hobby (HOU, smaller, mostly domestic). Both work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-16 grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12 items-start">
    <div class="md:col-span-7">
      <span class="block text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[color:var(--color-clay)] mb-3">Where to stay</span>
      <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-4xl tracking-tight mb-6">Near NRG, or near everything else?</h2>
      <p class="text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)] mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        There are two valid strategies. Stay <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">near NRG</strong> (Medical Center, NRG Park hotels) for short rides to matches but quieter evenings. Or stay <strong class="text-[color:var(--color-ink)]">downtown or in Montrose</strong> for better food, bars, and walkability — then ride out to NRG on match days. Light rail (METRORail) runs directly from downtown and Museum District to the stadium.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)] leading-relaxed">
        Hotels near NRG sell out months in advance for major events. Book as early as you can.
      </p>
      <a href="/hotels" class="mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium border-b border-[color:var(--color-ink)] pb-1 hover:text-[color:var(--color-clay)] hover:border-[color:var(--color-clay)] transition-colors">
        Full hotel guide
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M13 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
      </a>
    </div>

    <aside class="md:col-span-5 bg-[color:var(--color-ink)] text-[color:var(--color-paper)] p-8">
      <span class="block text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[color:var(--color-gold)] mb-4">Quick checklist</span>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">→</span> Book hotel as early as possible.</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">→</span> Confirm match tickets via FIFA's official channels.</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">→</span> Plan transit: METRORail goes downtown ↔ NRG.</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">→</span> Pack for heat & sudden rain; AC indoors is fierce.</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">→</span> Reserve dinner. Houston restaurants fill up on match days.</li>
        <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-[color:var(--color-gold)]">→</span> Bring a hat. NRG tailgating gets sun.</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-6 py-16">
    <span class="block text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-[color:var(--color-clay)] mb-3">Between matches</span>
    <h2 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-4xl tracking-tight mb-8">If you have a free day in Houston</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-px bg-[color:var(--color-ink)]/10 md:grid-cols-3">
      <a href="/things-to-do" class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8 hover:bg-[color:var(--color-paper)] transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl mb-3">Beat the heat</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">Museum District is fully air-conditioned and has nineteen options inside a walkable radius. The MFAH and Menil are the heavyweights.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/things-to-do" class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8 hover:bg-[color:var(--color-paper)] transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl mb-3">See space</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">Space Center Houston is a half-day, easy to combine with Kemah Boardwalk for a south-of-town day.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/restaurants" class="bg-[color:var(--color-cream)] p-8 hover:bg-[color:var(--color-paper)] transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-2xl mb-3">Eat one big meal</h3>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">Texas BBQ, original-recipe Tex-Mex, or Viet-Cajun crawfish. Houston earns its food reputation — don't miss your chance.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
